## User Guide

The Kiln Watcher is a "watchdog" program. It sits quietly in the background and asks the main controller for a status update every 5 seconds. If it detects a major event or a dangerous condition, it instantly sends a push notification to your phone.

### Standard Notifications

The watcher keeps you informed of your firing progress without requiring you to constantly check the web UI.

* ⚡ **POWER RESTORED:** Sent when the watcher first boots up. If you receive this randomly, your house or shop experienced a power outage.
* 🔥 **STARTED:** Sent when a profile begins running.
* 🎯 **TARGET REACHED:** Sent when a heating ramp finishes and the actual temperature lands within 3°C of the requested Setpoint.
* ✅ **ENDED:** Sent when a profile completes or is manually aborted. It includes the total run duration and the maximum temperature reached.
* 🔄 **AUTO-RESUMED:** Sent if the main controller recovers from a power loss and automatically restarts the firing schedule.

### Safety Alarms & Interlocks

The watcher acts as a secondary layer of logic to detect hardware failures that the main controller might not catch.

* 🌋 **RUNAWAY DETECTED (Alert):** Triggers if the physical temperature rises dangerously above your Setpoint (default is 30°C over). This usually means a Solid State Relay has failed in the "Closed/ON" position.
* ❄️ **RUNAWAY CLEARED:** Sent if the runaway temperature falls back into a safe range, letting you know the danger has passed.
* 🔌 **OPEN LOOP DETECTED (Alert):** Triggers if the controller is commanding 95% to 100% power for 5 continuous minutes, but the temperature has risen less than 3°C. This indicates either a broken heating element or a thermocouple that has slipped out of the kiln chamber.
* 🚨 **SYSTEM ERROR (Alert):** Triggers if the main controller reports a hardware fault, such as a disconnected or short-circuited thermocouple sensor.
